{
  "texts": [
    "• FreshQA (Vu et al, 2023).",
    "The FreshQA dataset functions as a dynamic QA benchmark, encompassing 600 English evaluation samples.",
    "Questions presented to LLMs are classified into four categories based on the characteristics of the answers: answers that remain constant, answers that undergo gradual changes, answers that undergo rapid changes, and answers with incorrect premises.",
    "This evaluation scrutinizes whether LLMs manifest hallucinatory phenomena in responding to questions and their ability to refute erroneous factual assumptions without succumbing to misdirection.",
    "• HalluQA (Cheng et al, 2023)."
  ]
}